  title `Short title.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_1_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00029_197672_1517807322415&sectionId=32373&sectionno=1&orderno=1&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00029_197672_1517807322415
obj_root_law_sections_1_content:
  string
  line `This Act may be called the Life Insurance Corporation (Modification of Settlements)`
  line `Act, 1976.`
obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_2:
  sectionId (32374)
  sectionNo (2)
  orderNo 2
  title Definitions.
  content obj_root_law_sections_2_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00029_197672_1517807322415&sectionId=32374&sectionno=2&orderno=2&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00029_197672_1517807322415
obj_root_law_sections_2_content:
  string
  line `In this Act, unless the context otherwise requires,--`
  line
  line `(a) "Corporation" means the Life Insurance Corporation of India established under section 3 of`
  line `the Life Insurance Corporation Act, 1956 (31 of 1956);`
  line
  line `(b) "salary" means basic pay and includes--`
  line
  line `(i) special pay, if any;`
  line
  line `(ii) dearness allowance; and`
  line
  line `(iii) additional dearness allowance;`
  line
  line `(c) "settlements" means,--`
  line
  line `(i) the settlement which was arrived at between the Corporation and their workmen on the`
  line `24th day of January, 1974, under section 18, read with clause (p) of section 2, of the Industrial`
  line `Disputes Act, 1947 (14 of 1947); and`
  line
  line `(ii) the settlement which was arrived at between the Corporation and their workmen on the`
  line `6th day of February, 1974, under section 18, read with clause (p) of section 2, of the said Act and`
  line `in respect of the terms of which there was no approval as provided for in sub-clause (2) of clause`
  line `12 thereof.`
obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_3:
  sectionId (32375)
  sectionNo (3)
  orderNo 3
  title `Modification of settlements.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_3_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00029_197672_1517807322415&sectionId=32375&sectionno=3&orderno=3&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00029_197672_1517807322415
obj_root_law_sections_3_content:
  string
  line `Notwithstanding anything contained in the Industrial Disputes Act,`
  line `1947 (14 of 1947),the provisions of each of the settlements, in so far as they relate to the payment of an`
  line `annual cash bonus to every Class III and Class IV employee of the Corporation at the rate of fifteen per`
  line `cent. of his annual salary, shall not have any force or effect and shall not be deemed to have had any force`
  line `or effect on and from the 1st day of April, 1975.`
obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes:
  string
  line
